04/09/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Combined Endeavour 2009, a United States European Command (USEUCOM) sponsored training exercise, began on Thursday (September 3rd) at the Kozara military barracks in Banja Luka. A total of 500 participants from 16 NATO member states, as well as about 150 Bosnian troops are participating in the drills that last through September 17th. US Defence AttachÃ© Michael Schleicher says the exercise aims to improve the use of telecommunications equipment and procedures used by the armed forces of NATO countries. The drills are taking place simultaneously in BiH, the Netherlands and Denmark. (RTRS, Srna, BHRT, Fena - 03/09/09)
